2.00	Hoax	Hoax	A hoax is a deliberately fabricated falsehood made to masquerade as truth. It is distinguishable from errors in observation or judgment, or rumors, urban legends, pseudosciences or April Fools' Day events that are passed along in good faith by believers or as jokes.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/75/Virginia_Woolf_in_Dreadnought_Hoax.jpg/220px-Virginia_Woolf_in_Dreadnought_Hoax.jpg
